# Coordination Documentation Edits

When modifying files under `docs/coordination/` or `AGENTS.md`:

1. Follow `docs/DOCUMENTATION_GOVERNANCE.md` — English canonical for technical prose.
2. Update `docs/coordination/DOCUMENTATION_INVENTORY.md` when adding/removing top-level coordination `.md`/`.yaml`.
3. Run `npm run control:validate` after material changes.
4. Control-plane sessions may update only the limited documents listed in `AGENTS.md` without separate permission.
5. Implementation agents must not update control docs unless task scope explicitly includes them.
6. Keep `ORCHESTRATION_STATE.md` §0 aligned with `TASK_REGISTRY.yaml` queues and locks.

Protocol documents (CORE) must stay consistent with the Runtime × Protocol matrix in `AGENTS.md`.
